Antenna.
Ten segmented and filiform; 849 ± 131 (708–986) µm long, 0.7 ± 0.1 (0.52–0.73) of total body length. Scape 47 ± 2.7 (44–49) µm long, with 2 or 3 setae. Pedicel 60 ± 7 (49–68) µm long, with 6–10 setae. Lengths of segments III–X (µm): III, 124 ± 21 (102–151); IV, 104 ± 28 (73–136); V, 100 ± 17 (78–119); VI, 99 ± 22 (73–122); VII, 86 ± 14 (73–102); VIII, 79 ± 11 (66–92); IX, 73 ± 10 (61–83); X, 78 ± 8 (68–88). Approximate number of setae on each of segments III–X: 
